The management of Durban's Addington Hospital is being accused of hiding information about the COVID-19 infection rate at the facility. It's alleged at least four nurses were placed in isolation after testing positive. DURBAN - The management of Durban's Addington Hospital is being accused of hiding information about the COVID-19 infection rate at the facility. It is alleged at least four nurses were placed in isolation after testing positive. READ: Parts of KZN may remain on Level 5 lockdown KwaZulu-Natal has the third-highest number of COVID-19 cases in the country, with eThekwini being the province's epicentre. KZN Department of Health MEC, Nomagugu Simelane-Zulu denied that the province is concealing the number of infections during a virtual briefing on health and social services with the Minister of Health, Dr Zweli Mkhize on Monday morning. Simelane-Zulu said when the nurse tested positive she informed everyone and all contacts were traced. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs